
=Description=

Excerpted from the [[Permacommons]]:

Refi.Sicilia:

"The goal of the DAB is to balance the holistic health of the biosphere as measured through vitality. How do we coordinate capital to finance the acquisition and development of Community Land Trusts? With a decentralized autonomous bioregion (DAB) of course! A DAB is the equivalent to a DAO with a dedicated staking node supporting it, with the prime objective being to manage a portfolio of properties for ecovillage development of land and sea rehabilitation. Architecturally, a DAB is a cosmos hub, with each ecovillage being a spoke. The DAB acts as the TRUSTEE of the community land trust, and ecovillages lease the land on renewing 99 year leases.


DABs as bioregional resources indexes to coordinate info around TCRs

- Food and food support systems 

- Shelter and Buildings 

- Livelihoods and support services 

- Info, media, communications, and research 

- Community and Security 

- Social Life 

- Health Services 

- Transport Services

Even with ETH2.0 scaling efforts we will live in a multichain world. Diversity is healthy. Cosmos’ architecture is unique in that each application is running on a dedicated blockchain, that can communicate with all the other blockchains through the Cosmos Hub, and the interblockchain communication (IBC) protocol."

